# Template Adoption Walkthrough ([PROJECT_NAME])

Read when:
- First time installing templates-v2 into a project.
- Adopting templates-v2 into a project that already exists ("retrofit").
- Re-checking adoption completeness when something feels missing ("AI keeps not using script X").

Skip when: routine feature work after adoption is fully green.

> This file is **distinct** from:
> - `docs/APPLY_CHECKLIST.md` — only checks "did you copy the files."
> - `docs/TEMPLATE_VALIDATION_CHECKLIST.md` — checks "did the files validate."
>
> This walkthrough checks "do you have each **capability** the template provides, AND has the AI been told how to discover it?" Adoption isn't done until every capability box is checked OR explicitly marked N/A with rationale.

The known failure mode this prevents: AI partially adopts a template (copies the docs, skips the scripts and CI), and on later sessions silently ignores capabilities that exist but were never wired up. The bottom of every section says exactly which trigger to register in `docs/CONTEXT_ROUTING.md` so future sessions discover the capability without burning startup tokens reading it.

---

## How to Use This Walkthrough

1. Work top to bottom. Do not skip sections.
2. For each capability:
   - Check whether it's present in the project.
   - If missing, copy from the listed source path.
   - Register the listed trigger in `docs/CONTEXT_ROUTING.md` § Event Triggers.
   - Run the listed proof command and confirm exit 0.
3. Mark each box `[x]` only when proof passed.
4. Marking `N/A` requires a one-line rationale next to the box.
5. At the end, run the final gate command. If green, adoption is complete.

